docs.lead_paragraph: The Senate met at 8 o' clock this evening. Debate arose on the question of approving the journal, a motion being made to expunge all relating to Mr. SPINOLA'S remarks at Friday's session. After opposition by Messrs. DOREBTT, ELT and PHAZZ, the journal was approved.

docs.snippet: The Isabel, at Charleston, from Havana, Jan. 25, brings the following commercial advices: In the sugar market there has been some little movement on speculation accounts, but without any change in quoted values.
